[5] USA (New York): students without vaccinations barred from school
Date: Mon 8 Apr 2019
Source: NY Post [abridged, edited]
https://nypost.com/2019/04/08/city-orders-yeshivas-to-bar-students-without-measles-vaccinations/


"This outbreak is being fueled by a small group of anti-vaxxers in these neighborhoods, said Health Commissioner Oxiris Barbot. "They have been spreading dangerous misinformation based on fake science."

The department says that 246 of the 285 cases are children and 39 are adults; 21 people have been hospitalized - including 5 admitted to intensive care units -- but there have been no deaths.

Last month [March 2019], the Health Department put the total at 158 cases.

Officials attributed much of the recent surge to Yeshiva Kehilath Yakov in Williamsburg allowing unvaccinated kids back into school or daycare. They said the yeshiva is connected to more than 40 cases, nearly double the 21 cases reported there a month ago.

However, the Health Department says the school is now in compliance with the exclusion order.

The new order is more expansive than the one issued in December [2018] affecting only schools in selected zip codes in Williamsburg and Borough Park.

[Byline: Rich Calder]

