[7] USA (Michigan, Oakland and Washtenaw County)
Date: Mon 8 Apr 2019
Source: WWJ Newsradio 950 [abridged, edited]
https://wwjnewsradio.radio.com/articles/measles-outbreak-spreads-washtenaw-county-41-cases-confirmed


Washtenaw County is reporting its 1st confirmed case of the measles as the number of infected in Michigan continues to rise. Issuing an update on the outbreak on [Mon 8 Apr 2019], the Michigan Department of Health and Human Services (MDHHS) said it has confirmed 2 additional measles cases, bringing the state total to 41 for this year [2019].

The newly confirmed cases are in Oakland and Washtenaw counties, with 39 of those cases in Oakland County, one in Washtenaw County and one in Wayne County. Infected individuals range in age from 8 months to 63 years-old.

MDHHS is working closely with the Oakland County Health Division and Washtenaw County Health Department to identify possible exposure locations for these latest cases. There are dozens of stores, schools and other public buildings already identified as exposure locations, which means anyone who recently visited the locations could have been infected. A complete list of known exposure sites and corresponding dates in Oakland County is listed at <Oakgov.com/health>.

Exposure locations are not yet available for the Washtenaw County case, officials said, and will be provided once available at <washtenaw.org/health>. There are no public exposure sites for the Wayne County case.

