[10] Hong Kong: airport
Date: 7 Apr 2019
Source: South China Morning News [abridged, edited]
https://www.scmp.com/news/hong-kong/health-environment/article/3005052/another-hong-kong-airport-worker-confirmed-having


Another Hong Kong airport worker has been confirmed as having measles, bringing this year's [2019] infection figures to 56.

The 30-year-old man, who worked at a restaurant in Terminal 2, developed fever on Thu 4 Apr 2019 and rash the following day.

One more airport staff member was confirmed to be infected with measles on Sun 7 Apr 2019, bringing the total number of people affected by the contagious disease in Hong Kong this year [2019] to 56.

The 56 measles cases recorded so far this year [2019] have been nearly 4 times the 15 cases in the whole of last year. Of them, 26 involved airport or airline personnel.

